mixin br
	br
//- -----------------------------------


section
	h2 Radio Input

	p <code>#{'<input>'}</code> elements of type <code>#{'radio'}</code> are generally used in radio groupsâ€”collections of radio buttons describing a set of related options. Only one radio button in a given group can be selected at the same time. Radio buttons are typically rendered as small circles, which are filled or highlighted when selected.

	form
		fieldset
			legend Please select your preferred contact method:
			label(for='fm-rdio1') Music:
				input#fm-rdio1(type='radio', name='contact' value='email')
			label(for='fm-rdio2') Phone:
				input#fm-rdio2(type='radio', name='contact' value='phone' checked)
			label(for='fm-rdio3') Mail:
				input#fm-rdio3(type='radio', name='contact' value='mail')
			+br
			button(type='submit') Submit
